New Hot Spring Found on Lake Chon of Mt. Paektu 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- A combined team to explore Lake Chon on Mt. Paektu succeeded in finding out a new hot spring on the lake.
 It already discovered a spring containing sodium bicarbonate of good quality and efficacious for medical treatment around the shore of the lake at the foot of Janggun Peak in the winter of Juche 73 (1984). Later the spring was named Paektu Hot Spring.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the course of intensive survey and expedition the members of the team found out a spring of 47.5 degrees centigrade at the foot of Rakwon Peak not far from the place where Janggun Peak, Hyangdo Peak and Haebal Peak stand in a row. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The spring also contains sodium bicarbonate of good quality and efficacious for medical treatment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The recent discovery of the spring is very instrumental in studying the geographical features of the lake to add shine to the natural and geographical treasure of the country.

Study Organization Inaugurated in Ukraine 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- The Ukrainian Association of Journalists and Men of Culture for the Study of Kimjongilism, "Sun of Juche", was formed with due ceremony in Kiev on May 5.
 A congratulatory speech was made at the ceremony by Nikolai Polishk, chairman of the Ukrainian "Treasured Sword of Songun" Association for the Study of the Juche Idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief of the Kiev City Organization of the Ukrainian "Treasured Sword of Songun" Association for the Study of the Juche Idea was elected chairman of the above-said association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that under the present situation the study of the Songun idea is urgently required not only by the Korean people but the world peoples who value independence and dignity, adding that the members of the association would deeply study the great Songun idea and theories and make efforts to embody them in practice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An action plan of the association was discussed there.

British Association Posts Special Write-ups on Internet 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- The British Association for the Study of the Songun Policy posted on Internet homepage a special write-up titled "By establishing the great tradition of great national unity" with a photo of President Kim Il Sung in the period of the anti-Japanese armed struggle.
 The write-up said that 70 years have passed since Kim Il Sung founded the Association for the Restoration of the Fatherland, the first organization of the anti-Japanese national united front in Korea, adding that he is the peerless patriot who rallied broad masses to achieve the liberation of the country through an all-out resistance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It quoted a south Korean media article as highly praising his exploits of great national unity. It stressed it is the faith cherished deep in the hearts of the south Korean people that his idea of great national unity will be carried forward and national reunification certainly be achieved by leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Another write-up titled "Let's smash the wild ambition of the Japanese reactionaries for reinvasion" disclosed the moves of the Japanese authorities to claim "dominium over Tok islet" and distort history. It expressed the conviction that progressive organizations of the world would extend positive support and solidarity to the Korean people in their struggle to foil the aggressive attempt of Japan with their united might.

Families of KPA Servicemen Give Performance 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- A performance was given by participants in the 9th contests of art groups of families of KPA servicemen at the People's Palace of Culture here on Monday.
 Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il recently appreciated a performance given by art groups of families of servicemen of different KPA units who had participated in the 9th contests. He noted with deep satisfaction that the performance was clear in political import, meeting the demand of the Songun era, and high in ideological and artistic plane and extended thanks to all the members of the art groups who displayed the proud features of the revolutionary soldier culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was appreciated by Kim Yong Nam, Pak Pong Ju, Jon Pyong Ho, Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop, Choe Yong Rim, Kim Kuk Thae, Kim Ki Nam, Vice-Premiers of the Cabinet Kwak Pom Gi, Ro Tu Chol and Jon Sung Hun, Chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party Kim Yong Dae, General of the KPA Pak Jae Gyong and officials of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The colorful program included a story telling and chorus "For the Motherland" highly praised by Kim Jong Il for its original depiction, and a chorus to the accompaniment of janggo beating, a poem and story telling, a poem recital and sketches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers sang in an excited tone of their boundless pride in preparing themselves as a large army of dependable women revolutionaries and growing as creators of the great art in the Songun era under the loving care of the outstanding brilliant commander of Songun. And they powerfully demonstrated the unshakable faith and will of all the servicemen's families to firmly take upon themselves one part of the Juche revolution as fighters of the forefront for defending the leader in the same trench with their husbands holding arms in their hands. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance was loudly applauded by the audience for giving satisfactory answers to important social and political questions in the Songun era and representing truthfully in an original way the life and sentiments of servicepersons' families.

"Assault on Pak Kun Hye" Branded as GNP's Self-Organized Terrorism 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification (Pomchonghakryon) reportedly made public a statement titled "Assault on Pak Kun Hye is GNP's self-organized terrorism" on May 26.
 The "assault" on Pak Kun Hye, representative of the Grand National Party of south Korea, on May 20 was a fraudulent drama, a political plot committed by the U.S. and pro-American conservative forces, the statement said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Finding it hard to deceive the people by floating stories about "pro-communist terrorism" as in the past, the U.S. and the GNP resorted to a new terrorism method this time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The political drama called "assault on Pak Kun Hye" was orchestrated against this backdrop. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This has set the stage for the GNP to get many votes in the "election", driving the forces for progressive reform into an unfavorable situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP is the sworn enemy of all the fellow countrymen as it seeks to deceive the people by cooking up such incident in the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people should not be taken in by this organized "terrorism" and the progressive reform forces should resolutely struggle against the GNP attempting to seize political power by fraud, distortion and plots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The progressive reform forces should reveal the truth behind the incident to the people and ostracize the GNP. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The South Headquarters of Pomchonghakryon will devotedly struggle for the destiny of the country with highest vigilance in the upcoming "local self-government election".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the participants in the "election" should positively vote for the progressive reform forces and foil the moves of the fraudulent and criminal group GNP for an overwhelming victory.

Joint Declaration of Elders Made Public in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- Elders of civic and social organizations in south Korea reportedly made public a joint declaration on May 26 on the occasion of the "local self-government election".
 The history of more than 60 years when the aspiration for independence was cruelly trampled down and division was forced by imperialism is a disgraceful history, said the joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It called upon all the conscientious forces to rally as one so as to prevent the Cold War and anti-national forces, who have persisted in inter-Korean confrontation and division with the backing of the foreign forces, from seizing power again. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea and political agitation of the anti-social, anti-national forces, which stoop to any infamy for power no matter whether a war may break out in this land or not, are incited by the "Grand National Party" and conservative media, it noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Urging all the people to participate in the "local self-government election", it said: They should vote for the progressive political party and politicians who will lead the future of society and the nation to progress and reform and administer new politics, not for the political group, party and politicians who aspire after the politics of corruptness and irregularities, sycophantic politics towards America, anti-reunification, anti-national politics and anti-social privileged politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It called for opening up a rosy future before the people and the nation with the forthcoming "election" as an occasion.

U.S. "War on Terrorism" and "Spread of Democracy" Bound to Go Bust 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- The U.S.-touted "war on terrorism" and "spread of democracy" is censured worldwide and is on the verge of total bankruptcy due to its reactionary and aggressive nature, says Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed article.
 Citing the results of a recent opinion poll on Bush conducted in the U.S. and a series of other information, the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush bellicose forces are falling deep into the pit they have dug themselves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What the popular masses desire is global peace and security based on justice and respect for sovereignty. Those dead-set against this desire and swimming against the trend of times are bound to meet severe punishment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. "war on terrorism" brings nothing but an evil cycle of terrorism and retaliation, social chaos and disorder. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Democracy can neither be exported nor imported. It is bound to get further mature in the course of meeting the people's wishes for independence through the exercise of sovereignty by each country. It is the people of each country who should judge themselves whether democracy is alive or not. The U.S., however, is working hard to impose "democracy" of its own style upon all countries of the world, advertising it as a "model." It is set to spread "democracy" through the "war on terrorism." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush forces' "war on terrorism" and "spread of democracy" is not aimed at ensuring freedom and peace but at attaining the selfish aim of the U.S. to dominate the world.

What Does GI's Note Forgery in S. Korea Show 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- Allen, soldier belonging to the U.S. second division in south Korea, was recently reported to have forged notes, lashing south Koreans from all walks of life into fury.
 According to investigation made by the south Korean police, he forged 20 U.S. dollar notes with the help of a computer and laser printer at his billet inside the unit before using them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This fact goes to prove that any American soldier can perpetrate such illegal act without difficulty as he pleases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He even forged south Korean notes and used them. One cannot rule out the possibility that the U.S. forces all over the world may forge notes of different countries where they are stationed and disturb financial order worldwide. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As already reported, the world has vehemently denounced the U.S. for conducting illegal dealings with lip-service to "war on terrorism" and "protection of financial order". Academic and press circles in many countries including the Netherlands, Austria and other European countries are becoming increasingly critical of the U.S. hypocritical nature. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present Bush administration and the Republican Party of the U.S. depend on the money provided by such illicit money launderers as the bankrupt Enron. The American economy is also kept afloat by dint of dirty money laundering. No wonder, Internet Homepage Conspiracy Planet on April 26 commented that but for the illicit money laundering the U.S. economy would have gone long bankrupt. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is a kingpin of illicit dealing and criminal financial transaction as it is disturbing the international financial order.

Rich Experience in Building Revolutionary Party
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- The Workers' Party of Korea has set a good example in building a revolutionary party through its protracted history full of ordeals.
 President Kim Il Sung delivered the lecture "The Historical Experience of Building the Workers' Party of Korea" on May 31, Juche 75 (1986), on the occasion of the 40th anniversary of the foundation of Kim Il Sung Higher Party School. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  He, in the work, analyzes and reviews in a comprehensive way the priceless achievements and rich experience gained in the process of building the Juche-oriented revolutionary Party, a new type of party of the working class. And he expounds the feature, character and mission of the WPK and the fundamental theory and basic principles of the Party-building. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work gives invaluable guidelines that should be taken in strengthening the working-class Party as the guide of socialist society. They include the importance and essence of the Party's leadership over the revolution and construction, issues of principle arising in the Party's leadership, and the essence and contents of the Party's leadership art and all the issues of principle arising in establishing its leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ideas and theories advanced in the work have served as a powerful weapon for having developed the WPK over the past two decades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the guidance of leader Kim Jong Il, the WPK has been firmly strengthened as Kim Il Sung's party, Juche-oriented revolutionary one, and held fast to the independent, working-class and socialist principles in the revolution and construction under grim and arduous historical circumstances. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK, therefore, has displayed its might as an invincible one without any slightest deviation in the revolutionary principles and errors in its lines. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For the revolutionary principles of the WPK and the consistency in its lines and policies, the Korean revolution has triumphantly advanced along the one road of socialism and the people-centered Korean-style socialism has deeply rooted in the minds of the people as an unswerving faith. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK is lauded by the world progressives as the mother party which has achieved the single-minded unity of the leader, the Party and the popular masses.

Research into Puffer Venom Deepened
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30, (KCNA) -- Efforts have been directed into the research on puffer venom in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 A technology of separating and purifying process for tetrodotoxin, the useful component of puffer venom, was established in recent years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Based on this success, the government has built a unit specializing in extracting tetrodotoxin from puffer venom. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Tetrodotoxin produced in the unit is being widely used in the fields of physiology and pharmacology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The puffer tetrodotoxin is efficacious for treating various kinds of diseases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The clinical tests of the tetrodocaine injection, puffer tuberculosis injection and other medicines made with tetrodotoxin have proved successful in the treatment of many diseases over the last decades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, the tetrodocaine injection (120MIU/1ml) is potent for the treatment of nasal cancer, pharyngeal cancer and cancer of the esophagus. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The application of the puffer tuberculosis injection (80MIU/2ml) alone is very effective against tuberculosis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Scientists are deepening researches into applying the injection (160MIU/2ml) to the treatment of medicinal poisoning, terminal cancer and heart disorders and the alleviation of pain.

Severe Punishment of GNP Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- All the south Korean people should participate in the election to the  "local self-governing bodies" and severely punish the Grand National Party of south Korea advertising "its certain victory," urges Minju Joson Tuesday in a signed commentary.
 Accusing the GNP, which has more seats of major provincial and city governors than what all other parties and independents have, of using pro-American conservative media for staging even a charade to build up public opinion sympathetic with the GNP, the commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What should not be overlooked is that the GNP is spreading rumor that it can win a "sweeping victory" in the "election." This is nothing but a product of the wicked intention to make the GNP's sure victory an established fact and pressurize progressive forces for reform abstain from voting. The GNP group is busy wooing foreign media report about the GNP's "possible sweeping victory." Playing into their hands, some foreign media do not bother to release stories that the GNP may "take posts of all major provincial and city governors." Other parties are also calling for deterring the GNP from winning a sweeping victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the GNP is allowed to do so in the election, it is as clear as noonday that on that basis it will seize power through the "presidential election" to be held next year and what adverse consequences will be entailed by this will be as plain as a pikestaff. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality today when the GNP is behaving so requires the south Korean people to get awakened and mete out a stern judgement to the treacherous party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Action is more important than mere talking on the eve of election. Whoever loves the country and the nation, sets store by the June 15 joint declaration and does not want war should not be taken in by the treacherous party's trick but turn out in the struggle to crush it.

Asos Branded as Family of Bloodsuckers
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- The family of Japanese Foreign Minister Aso has been known as a family of bloodsuckers for many generations as it press-ganged people of other countries into hard labor and accumulated wealth at the cost of their sweat and blood, observes Minju Joson Tuesday in a signed commentary.
 The Asos' history is just an epitome of the criminal history of Japan, the commentary notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan has not yet compensated its victims although half a century has passed since the end of the Second World War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The same holds true for Aso. He should have felt ashamed of the inglorious past history of his family and repented of it, though belatedly. But there is no sign of his feeling such moral responsibility. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He, on the contrary, has justified and whitewashed his family's criminal history. This is clearly proved by what he uttered when he was active as minister of Public Management. He asserted that "there was not such thing as forcible drafting" and "Japan just permitted Koreans to change their names into Japanese as they wanted it." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is self-evident that he can't be otherwise as he has inherited the tradition of the criminal family just as a crow can not turn out to be a white heron. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It can not but be a tragedy of the Japanese political camp that a descendent of such shameful family is keen to be a frontrunner in the political arena though he deserves curse and censure from all people. No wonder, there are not a few heavyweights in the Japanese political camp at present who have similar family backgrounds as Aso. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is not hard to guess which way Japan will go as descendents of such war criminals are still at large. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is now censured as the sworn enemy of the Korean nation and as enemy of humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK will certainly force Japan to pay for all the damage and humiliation imposed upon the Koreans by the Japanese imperialists in the past.

Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Unit 215
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, inspected KPA Unit 215 honored with the title of O Jung Hup-led Seventh Regiment.
 After being saluted, he looked round the room devoted to the unit's history.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the unit should always remember the benevolence bestowed upon it by President Kim Il Sung, noting that it grew stronger to be a matchless combat unit thanks to his wise guidance and meticulous instructions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly appreciated the successes made by the unit, recalling that it has taken the lead in upholding the WPK's Songun leadership in the defence of the country and at socialist construction sites. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After watching the training of the command staff, he expressed satisfaction over the fact that the commanding officers of the unit are paying primary attention to the training aimed to acquire a high level of military technique and commanding ability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Going round a servicepersons' hall, a library, a video recording and wire broadcasting room and other entertainment and educational facilities, he praised the unit for conducting diverse politico-ideological work in a unique manner to suit the characteristic features of its servicepersons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After being told that there is growing enthusiasm among the soldiers to study through the library, he appreciated this as a very good thing. He noted that a revolutionary should study regularly and study and study till the last moments of his or her life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Watching the barracks clad in the thick verdure of various species of trees and their compound kept neat and tidy, he highly praised the unit for having spruced up the compound like a park. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then he made the rounds of supply service facilities. He was greatly satisfied with the good living conditions provided to the soldiers and indicated tasks to be tackled to improve the supply service and ways to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly appreciated the achievements made by the unit in its work to implement the WPK's military line. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photograph taken with the servicepersons of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Hwang Pyong So, vice department director of the Central Committee of the WPK.
